Chrome 77 appears to have changed some rendering logic with elements that contain float, top and transform css properties. We use these properties to vertically center elements inside containers that have a fixed height. I suspect it might be something to do with [this change][1]. 

I have replicated the issue in a very simple test case: 

index.html: 

    &lt;html&gt;
      &lt;head&gt;
        &lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot;&gt;
        &lt;meta http-equiv=&quot;X-UA-Compatible&quot; content=&quot;IE=edge&quot;&gt;
        &lt;link rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; href=&quot;styles.css&quot;/&gt;
        &lt;title&gt;testing&lt;/title&gt;
      &lt;/head&gt;
      &lt;body&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;container&quot;&gt;
          &lt;div class=&quot;child&quot;&gt;Testing&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/body&gt;
    &lt;/html&gt;

styles.css:

    .container {
      width: 300px;
      height: 100px;
      position: relative;
      background-color: yellow;
      overflow: auto;
    }
    
    .child {
      position: relative;
      float: left;
      top: calc(50% - 100vh);
      transform: translateY(-50%) translateY(100vh);
    }

[Here is the jsfiddle][2]. If you view it in Chrome 77, the yellow div has a vertical scrollbar which scrolls down a long way (the height of vh). If you view it on Chrome &lt;= 76 (or any other browser) it does not. 

The problem is solved by changing the top and transform properties to the following: 

    .child {
      position: relative;
      float: left;
      top: calc(50%);
      transform: translateY(-50%);
    }

However, the reason why the 100vh is subtracted and added was to work around an IE and Edge issue where a vertical scroll bar would appear if .child had a height &gt;= 50% of the .container height. By removing the 100vh to fix the Chrome 77 issue, we have now reintroduced the IE and Edge issue. 

Does anyone have a solution for vertically centering elements on all browsers including Chrome 77? 


  [1]: https://developers.google.com/web/updates/2019/06/layoutNG#floats
  [2]: https://jsfiddle.net/4rn5hq7y/

